<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="833" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hardy</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-16"><hi rend="italic">February 16,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hardy reports that he has been informed by the minister for foreign
                            affairs that before the Government of Spain can follow the example of
                            the Governments of France, Germany, and Great Britain it must first be
                            informed of the text of their adherence to the note of the United States
                            Government.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>